🌟 Core Concepts
Routing: Maps specific URLs to Python functions using the @app.route() decorator.
Debug Mode: Activating debug=True automatically restarts the local server whenever code changes are detected.
Jinja2 Templating: Used to render dynamic variables and control flows directly inside HTML files.
Extensibility: Easily plugs into third-party extensions for advanced features like database ORMs (SQLAlchemy), authentication, and form validation.


89. Django
Django is a high level,open source Python web framework that follows the MVT architecture and provides built-in features such as ORM, authentication, security, and an admin panel.

MVT architecture
Model: The data interface. It defines your database schema using standard Python code, allowing you to manipulate records via an Object-Relational Mapper (ORM) instead of raw SQL.
View: The request handler. It contains the backend logic that accepts HTTP requests, communicates with the Model, and returns the appropriate HTTP response or template.
Template: The presentation layer. These are text or HTML files mixed with the Django Template Language (DTL) to dynamically render data passed from the views.

